<seg id=1> The Irish Republic Army Declares Cease-fire </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, London.  August 31st, Reporter: Li Wenhao. The Irish Republic Army declared today that from this night on the organization would stop all military activities and to enact a "non-conditional and non-periodic" cease-fire. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Irish Republic Army noted, in a declaration to the media of the UK and Ireland, that in consideration of the current situation and to promote the peace process, the IRA made the cease-fire decision and notified all of its troops. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The avowal requests that the UK government accept responsibility for the undertaking, and urges all relevant parties to face the situation that is brought by the cease-fire with firmness and patience.  Furthermore, it requests that the governments of the UK and Ireland as well as all the main parties in North Ireland work together towards resolving the conflict in North Ireland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The avowal says, the cease-fire announcement made by the Irish Republic Army provides opportunities for "justice and permanent settlement" in North Ireland disputes. </seg>
<seg id=6> However, the Irish Republic Army also reiterated it would still keep "the republic target", i.e. the unification of the whole island. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The Irish Republic Army's struggle to realize the unification of North Ireland with the Republic of Ireland has resulted in 25 long and violent years. </seg>
</p>
